<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Holding down reset in an emulator]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11405&amp;p=130871#p130871"><![CDATA[
Soft reset detection is just reading two bytes from RAM to see if they match what your program put there when it started. Perhaps unlicensed games using a negative voltage stun circuit had to be smarter about that in order to not overload the CIC.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Jul 09, 2014 12:01 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
