I don't really see the point of randomizing it, at least not for a regular user who wants to just play games that work. For someone who needs to do debugging, though, if your debugger let you alter the input/reset states during a breakpoint, this would let you test the effect of these things at any point. Maybe if you had a virtual gamepad UI where instead of taking input from the keyboard/joypad you could toggle buttons and reset on and off by clicking them?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> — Tue Jul 08, 2014 11:46 am</p><hr />
